OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1772572325
OL,3,CViolence against women and girls 'the
OL,4,Cpriority': new Cumbria Chief Constable
OL,6,FOn violence against women and girls,
OL,7,Fhe said: "I would say (this) is the
OL,8,Fpriority. Cumbria Constabulary and the
OL,9,Fpolice service are really
OL,10,Funderstanding what the causes are.
OL,12,F"One of the things that we find is
OL,13,Fpeople on occasions be frightened to
OL,14,Fcome forward. I'd encourage people -
OL,15,F(we) need to you tell us. But I need
OL,16,FCumbria Constabulary to give victims
OL,17,Fthe confidence to come forward.
OL,26,@oD@WpmoD@\pnwD@ApmwD@Dpn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/7
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1772572325
OL,3,CViolence against women and girls 'the
OL,4,Cpriority': new Cumbria Chief Constable
OL,6,F"And that's a matter through dealing
OL,7,Fwith things promptly, taking
OL,8,Fenforcement action and providing that
OL,9,Freassurance to victims."
OL,11,FAnother key area of focus for the new
OL,12,FChief Constable is anti-social
OL,13,Fbehaviour.
OL,15,FMartland said: "It is a significant
OL,16,Fpriority for Cumbria Constabulary. I'm
OL,17,Fvery much into prevention as opposed
OL,18,Fto cure.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/7
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1772572325
OL,3,CViolence against women and girls 'the
OL,4,Cpriority': new Cumbria Chief Constable
OL,6,F"I want to get ahead of it, I want to
OL,7,Fprevent it. And the way to do that is
OL,8,Fworking with communities through our
OL,9,Fneighbourhood policing model. And I'm
OL,10,Fdelighted to say that we have a well-
OL,11,Festablished police model that works.
OL,13,F"But what I want to do is develop and
OL,14,Fenhance that, by putting more officers
OL,15,Finto neighbourhoods."
OL,17,FChief Constable Martland also
OL,18,Femphasised the importance of
OL,19,Fneighbourhood policing when tackling
OL,20,Forganised crime.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/7
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1772572325
OL,3,CViolence against women and girls 'the
OL,4,Cpriority': new Cumbria Chief Constable
OL,6,F"Serious and organised crime is an
OL,7,Fissue. It's a national issue, and we
OL,8,Fdo have issues here in Cumbria,"
OL,9,FMartland said.
OL,11,F"It's very much about using a whole
OL,12,Fbreadth of tactics, but again this
OL,13,Fhappens in a neighbourhood.
OL,15,F"So core to this is neighbourhood
OL,16,Fpolicing. They are the eyes and ears
OL,17,Fof communities: listening, engaging
OL,18,Fand gaining trust and confidence so
OL,19,Fcommunities give us the information to
OL,20,Fenable us to take action."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/7
